{
  "stem": "9102.2",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "It's not where-- you know, because having-- in university, you probably had to go in the officer's training.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "But I just didn't like.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "So I had decided to move to Canada.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Those people, I should mention, also who lived in Heerlen downstairs, they had moved to Canada in 1954.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "So my aunt, when I lived with them in Heerlen, she says well, OK, I'll go with you.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Because we go to Winnipeg where they moved to.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And then we go from there.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "So in the meantime, I had-- well, I had met my-- my wife, and whatever you want to call it, in Holland-- and said, you know-- your girlfriend.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And, you know, I moved over in '58.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And I was here.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "I ask her if she wanted to come over and marry me, which she did in '59.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Lammy.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My wife's name is Lammy.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "She, in that time, in '58, I had to sign that we got-- we had to marry within 30 days.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That was the Canadian law.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "She arrived in July.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we had to get married within 30 days.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Or she had to go back to the-- to Holland again.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So we got married in September-- August the 12th in 1959 here in Canada, in Winnipeg.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Certainly.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, right after the war-- I guess that was even already in '44-- the Dutch government started to pay for me, because I probably was-- because I was an orphan.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And, well, that was in '45 then, of course.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I was from Jewish heritage.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they have paid all along till 1958.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The Dutch government has paid my studies, going to university.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Every week my aunt had to go and pick up the-- the weekly allowance or whatever it was-- what she-- what she lived on.",
      "word_count": 24
    }
  ],
